--- Message 23 (microsoft_teams) ---
From: snigdha
Time: 2026-06-10T21:24:22.535Z
Teams message id: 1781126662535
Text: More on Phantom 👻:
• What it is — an autonomous browser-automation agent that takes plain-language tasks from chat and carries them out in a real browser, then reports back.
• Brain — Claude Code reads PHANTOM_SPEC.md, plans, and decides what to click/type/navigate (no hardcoded agent loop).
• Hands & eyes — a Playwright toolkit: an Observer (screenshots + accessibility tree with numbered Set-of-Mark labels) and an Actions module with self-healing selectors (ID/text/aria/CSS fallbacks).
• Persistent browser — Chromium runs as a background server on port 9222; tasks connect via CDP so cookies, tabs and login state survive across tasks.
• Stealth — anti-bot evasion + human-like mouse movement; VNC lets a human step in when needed.
• Surfaces — Slack is primary; Microsoft Teams (this branch) and WhatsApp are experimental PoCs.
• Extras — persistent memory file, Flask dashboard on port 9000, web search (Tavily), and systemd services for running continuously.
Ask me to run a task and I'll drive the browser for you!
